What you need to know:

By evading a full trial, Mr Tuju, perhaps, knew that he could not argue his case in the London court.With its diplomatic immunity, it had an upper hand, since Mr Tuju could not sue the bank — even if there were governance issues.EADB enjoys immunity from every form of legal process.Defeated in London, Mr Tuju — and as the bank pushes to sell his properties over the loan — has now gone to the Kenyan High Court.